 Chris Broad mum on son Stuart
OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENTKochi: The thrashing from Yuvraj Singh in the World Twenty20 notwithstanding, 21-year-old Stuart Broad figures among the most promising of cricketers. Indeed, the son of one-time England opener Chris isnt just a new ball-bowler with potential, but quite a decent bat. That was evident during the recent India versus England ODIs. Chris is in India as Match Referee for the ongoing India-Australia series, but declined to speak about Stuart. Ive promised my son I wont talk about him... Its just that both of us are apprehensive that something I say could get distorted. So, good or bad, Im keeping mum, he told The Telegraph. Chris didnt compromise as a cricketer and is known to be firm as a Match Referee. A rethink, therefore, is unlikely. 
